Seseorang Akan Mendapat Ujian Sebanding Kualitas Imannya;
.
Syaikhul Islam mengatakan,

واللهُ تَعَالَى قَدْ جَعَلَ أَكْمَلَ المُؤْمِنِيْنَ إِيْمَانًا أَعْظَمُهُمْ بَلاَءً “Allah akan memberikan cobaan terberat bagi setiap orang mukmin yang sempurna imannya.”[3]
.
Semakin kuat iman, semakin berat cobaan, namun semakin Allah cinta. Rasulullah shallallahu ‘alaihi wa sallam bersabda,

إِنَّ عِظَمَ الْجَزَاءِ مَعَ عِظَمِ الْبَلاَءِ وَإِنَّ اللَّهَ إِذَا أَحَبَّ قَوْمًا ابْتَلاَهُمْ فَمَنْ رَضِىَ فَلَهُ الرِّضَا وَمَنْ سَخِطَ فَلَهُ السَّخَطُ “Sesungguhnya balasan terbesar dari ujian yang berat. Jika Allah mencintai suatu kaum, maka Allah akan memberikan cobaan kepada mereka. Barangsiapa ridho, maka Allah pun ridho. Dan barangsiapa murka (tidak suka pada cobaan tersebut, pen), maka baginya murka Allah.”[6]
.
Source:
[3] Qo’idah fil Mahabbah, Syaikhul Islam Ibnu Taimiyah, hal. 150, Maktabah At Turots Al Islamiy.
.
[6] HR. Tirmidzi no. 2396, dari Anas bin Malik. Syaikh Al Albani mengatakan bahwa hadits ini hasan shahih.
.

Here's a liver with macronodular cirrhosis being observed in a surgery! 
Liver cirrhosis is an end result of an underlying pathology. It develops when scar tissue replaces the normal, healthy tissue of the  liver.
Notice the large nodules separated by wider scars are irregularly distributed throughout the liver, which occurs  usually due to an infectious agent such as viral hepatitis which does not diffuse uniformly throughout the liver. 
Usually, such liver damage cannot be reversed, but treatment can delay further progression and reduce complications. 
Liver transplantation is necessary when complications develop and liver cease to function.

@Regrann from @futurenp_ -  I get this question/comment often and almost everyday. "I'm too scared to start nursing school, I feel like I'm not good enough/ it's too hard." 🗣The first step is always the most difficult. If you keep putting it off, let's be realistic, it will never happen. Stop putting off that financial aid application, stop saying you're going to start your prerequisites, stop saying you're too old and stop saying you'll call the admissions advisor tomorrow. The time to do it is now. Saying you're scared only makes your decision to start that much harder. The next few years will pass quickly regardless if you're in nursing school or still sitting there doing nothing. Nursing school takes dedication + hard work. If there's a will, then there sure as hell is a way. I'm just sayin. - #regrann
